XIX. MARIUS.

Gaius Marius was born at Arpinum of a humble family. When the younger Scipio was waging war against the Span- iards, Marius began his military life,6 and showed great valor and enthusiasm. Then he himself waged war successfully against Jugurtha, being⁷ chosen consul in place of Metellus, whom he had accused of2 prolonging the war. Jugurtha was defeated8 and captured,8 and being7 taken to Rome, was at last put to death in prison.

A few years after this a great danger threatened Rome.
